2025-05-27 14:35:34 | INFO     | src.agents.conversation:process_query:174 - Content: Generally, CalPERS processes retirement payments on a monthly basis. The first retirement check is usually issued about 30 to 60 days after CalPERS receives a completed retirement application. However, the exact timing can vary depending on several factors, including the complexity of the application, the speed at which required documents are submitted, and the workload of the CalPERS processing team. 

It's also important to note that the first payment may be a partial payment, covering the period from the retirement date to the end of the month in which the first payment is made. Subsequent payments are typically made on the last working day of each month. 

To get a more precise estimate for your specific situation, it's recommended that you contact CalPERS directly. They can provide you with the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding your retirement application and payment schedule. 

Additionally, you can check the CalPERS website or consult your retirement benefits booklet for more detailed information on the retirement payment process and timeline. Remember, planning ahead and understanding the timeline for receiving your retirement checks can help you manage your finances effectively during this transition. 

Please keep in mind that the information provided is based on general guidelines and may be subject to change. For the most current and personalized information, always consult directly with CalPERS or visit their official website.
